<br>
Ready-to-punch-a-wall angry.  Played-for-a-sucker angry.<br>
<br>
I HATE it when you make an arrangement with someone, and they blow off their promises.  Even worse, try to renegotiate.  How can you trust someone like that?<br>
<br>
Over the last few weeks, I have been trying to find an Ogre Smith willing to do Fulvous Darkscale combines (having discovered that Trolls can wear FD, but cannot make it).  I checked the VCC Tradeskills board and left many notes asking for assistance, and what would be reasonable compensation.  Finally, Jhark of &lt;Call of Elders&gt; responded saying he would do skill-up combines for FREE, provided I was willing to accept 1) his skill was below Grandmaster 2) the likelihood of failure was high for more complicated pieces (bp, legs, etc) 3) all material costs were on me 4) I had to come prepared for the combine with all the necessary ingredients.<br>
<br>
I agreed to his terms, and asked him AGAIN if indeed he was not looking for any compensation.  He reiterated that no compensation was needed, since he wanted very much to skill-up.  He said he had to go to work, but would be back on-line in 10 hours.  I told him I would do my best to make sure that I would have everything ready for when he came back on-line.<br>
<br>
Since I was looking to do combines for the more difficult pieces, I knew I had to have plenty of materials for fails.  I started buying everything I still needed, arranged with a Shaman to do imbuing, arranged and paid an Enchanter to do the enchanting, and camped what I could.  12 hours and 14kpp later, Jhark logs back on and sends me a tell.<br>
<br>
He said he doesn't do skill-up combines for free anymore.<br>
<br>
***pause***<br>
<br>
So I asked him... what about our arrangement?  Was he lying before?  Had we not taked about this beforehand, and come to a deal?  He said he had just become &quot;educated&quot;.  I asked him how much would this &quot;education&quot; cost?  He said he had no idea.... and that he would get back to me on that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
